      <div xml:id="NA177-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu celavuk kuṟippaṟinta talaimakaḷ tōḻikku uraittatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what SHE who had understood [his] intention of going said to the confidante.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA177">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            parantupaṭu kūreri kāṉa naippa</l>
<l>            marantī yuṟṟa makiḻtalai yaṅkāṭ</l>
<l>            ṭotukkarum veñcura miṟantaṉar maṟṟavar</l>
<l>            kuṟippiṟ kaṇṭiciṉ yāṉē neṟippaṭa</l>
<l>            vēlu milaṅkilai tuṭaippa palakaiyum </l>
<l>            pīli cūṭṭi maṇiyaṇi pavvē</l>
<l>            peṇṭiṉu naṉipala vaḷippa viṉiyē</l>
<l>            vantaṉṟu pōlun tōḻi nontunon</l>
<l>            teḻuteḻi luṇkaṭ pāvai</l>
<l>            yaḻitaru veḷḷa nīntu nāḷē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>He has but gone to traverse<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">iṟantavar maṟṟu</term>: here the p.a. expresses the fact of the action being on its way, though not completed. What does the <term xml:lang="ta">maṟṟu</term> do here? Of all possible actions just this one?</note> the hot desert, difficult to control,</l>
<l rend="indent">of the [once] delightful pretty wilderness where the trees have caught fire,</l>
<l rend="indent2">while sharp flames, coming up [and] spreading, crush the forest.</l>
<l>I see his intention.<note place="foot">This and the next three main verbs are without temporal infix, which might either mean that they have to be taken with the rest as immediate past, or that they actualise what has taken place in the immediate past: SHE still sees HIM form the intention of going.</note></l>
<l rend="indent4">Orderly</l>
<l>he wipes the shining leaf of [his] spear and he puts</l>
<l>peacock-feathers on [his] shield [and] adorns it with bells.</l>
<l>And now he takes ever so much care of [his] wife.</l>
<l>It seems to have come, friend,</l>
<l rend="indent">the day of swimming the flood, the pupils of [my] kajal eyes,</l>
<l rend="indent2">graceful [as if] drawn, going to waste, aching, aching.</l>
        </lg>
